dct_title_s: Indiana-Illinois Princeton quadrangle [1949 printing with minor corrections]
dct_description_sm: Jno. H. Renshawe, geographer in charge , control by Geo. T. Hawkins , topography by Chas. W. Goodlove. Filing title: Princeton, Ind.-Ill. [Edition of] 1901, minor corrections made 1949. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Shows portion of Gibson County, Indiana, and small portions of Knox County, Indiana, and Wabash County, Illinois. "Culture revised in part, 1940 and 1949." "Minor corrections made 1949." "N3815-W8730/15."
Dimensions: 45 x 42 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:62,500
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); Goodlove, C. W.; Renshawe, John H.; Hawkins, Geo. T. (George T.)
